# Portfolio 2026 - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
Personal portfolio website built from Nuxt UI PRO Template for Ailen Gonzalez.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Nuxt 4.x with TypeScript
- **UI Library**: Nuxt UI 4.x (Tailwind CSS v4 + Reka UI)
- **Animations**: motion-v (Motion component)
- **State Management**: Vue composables with reactive state
- **Content**: @nuxt/content v3 with typed collections
- **Package Manager**: pnpm 10.x
- **CSS**: Tailwind CSS v4 (new @import syntax)
- **Icons**: Iconify (lucide & simple-icons)
- **Images**: @nuxt/image
- **OG Images**: nuxt-og-image
- **Utilities**: @vueuse/nuxt

## Project Structure
```
app/
├── components/          # Shared Vue components
│   ├── landing/        # Landing page specific components
│   │   ├── Hero.vue         # Hero with gradient title, social icons, tech logos
│   │   ├── About.vue        # Role tabs (Designer/Developer)
│   │   ├── Projects.vue     # Project grid (Self/Pet projects)
│   │   ├── Services.vue     # Service cards with wavy background
│   │   ├── Web3Quote.vue    # Blockchain/Web3 exploration quote
│   │   └── Contact.vue      # Contact CTA with email
│   ├── AppHeader.vue   # Fixed header with logo, nav, CTA
│   ├── AppFooter.vue   # Footer with social links
│   └── ColorModeButton.vue
├── composables/        # Global composables (auto-imported)
├── layouts/            # Page layouts
├── pages/              # Route pages (file-based routing)
├── assets/css/         # Global CSS (main.css)
├── utils/              # Shared utility functions
└── app.config.ts       # Runtime app configuration

content/
├── index.yml           # Homepage content
├── about.yml           # About page content
├── blog/               # Blog posts (markdown)
├── blog.yml            # Blog listing page
├── projects/           # Project entries (yml)
├── projects.yml        # Projects listing page
└── speaking.yml        # Speaking engagements

content.config.ts       # Content collection schemas (Zod)
nuxt.config.ts          # Nuxt configuration
```

## Nuxt UI 4.x Components
Prefer these Nuxt UI components:
- `UButton` - All buttons (solid, outline, subtle, soft, ghost, link variants)
- `UIcon` - Icons with iconify (i-lucide-*, i-simple-icons-*)
- `UModal` - Dialogs and modals
- `UCard` - Card layouts
- `UPageHero` - Page hero sections with slots (headline, title, description, links)
- `UPageSection` - Page content sections
- `UPage` - Page wrapper
- `UNavigationMenu` - Navigation menus
- `UColorModeAvatar` - Avatar with light/dark variants

## Styling Guidelines

### Priority: Use Tailwind CSS First
Always prefer Tailwind utility classes over custom CSS.
- Write styles using Tailwind classes directly in templates
- Only use `<style scoped>` for truly complex styles that Tailwind can't handle
- Use Tailwind's arbitrary values for one-offs: `class="mt-[17px]"`
- Leverage Tailwind's dark mode utilities

### Tailwind CSS v4 Syntax
This project uses Tailwind v4 with the new import syntax:
```css
@import "tailwindcss";
@import "@nuxt/ui";

@theme static {
  --font-sans: 'Public Sans', sans-serif;
  --font-serif: 'Instrument Serif', serif;
}
```

**Important v4 class names:**
- Use `bg-linear-to-*` instead of `bg-gradient-to-*`
- Use `shrink-0` instead of `flex-shrink-0`
- Use `aspect-4/3` instead of `aspect-[4/3]`

### Colors
Primary color is `violet`. Use Nuxt UI color tokens:
- Primary: `violet` (gradients: violet → fuchsia → orange)
- Neutral: `neutral`
- Semantic: `success`, `warning`, `error`, `info`

Use classes like:
- `bg-primary`, `text-primary`
- `bg-success`, `text-error`
- `text-muted`, `bg-muted`
- `bg-elevated`, `bg-default`
- `ring-default`, `ring-offset-(--ui-bg)`

### Typography
- Sans font: `font-sans` (Public Sans)
- Serif font: `font-serif` (Instrument Serif) - Use for emphasis/titles
- Italic serif for special headings: `font-serif italic`

## Vue Component Conventions

### Script Setup
```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
import type { SomeType } from '@nuxt/content'

const { config } = useAppConfig()

defineProps<{
  page: SomeType
}>()
</script>
```

### Props & Emits
- Use `defineProps<T>()` with TypeScript generics
- Use `defineEmits<T>()` with TypeScript generics
- Keep template logic minimal - use computed properties

### Animations with Motion-v
Use the `<Motion>` component for animations:
```vue
<Motion
  :initial="{ opacity: 0, y: 30 }"
  :animate="{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }"
  :transition="{ duration: 0.6, delay: 0.1 }"
>
  <!-- Content -->
</Motion>
```

For scroll-triggered animations:
```vue
<Motion
  :initial="{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }"
  :while-in-view="{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }"
  :transition="{ duration: 0.5, delay: 0.1 }"
  :in-view-options="{ once: true }"
>
```

Stagger animations with dynamic delays:
```vue
<Motion
  v-for="(item, index) in items"
  :key="index"
  :transition="{ duration: 0.6, delay: index * 0.1 }"
>
```

## Content Collections

### Defining Collections (content.config.ts)
Use Zod schemas with `defineCollection`:
```ts
import { defineCollection, defineContentConfig, z } from '@nuxt/content'

export default defineContentConfig({
  collections: {
    blog: defineCollection({
      type: 'page',        // or 'data' for non-page content
      source: 'blog/*.md',
      schema: z.object({
        title: z.string(),
        date: z.date(),
        // ...
      })
    })
  }
})
```

### Querying Content
```ts
const { data: posts } = await useAsyncData('blog', () =>
  queryCollection('blog').order('date', 'DESC').all()
)
```

## App Configuration (app.config.ts)
Runtime configuration for:
- `global.*` - Site-wide settings (picture, email, available status, meetingLink)
- `ui.*` - Nuxt UI component customizations
- `footer.*` - Footer links and credits

Access via:
```ts
const { global, footer } = useAppConfig()
```

## Naming Conventions

### Files
- Vue components: PascalCase (`Hero.vue`, `AppHeader.vue`)
- Composables: camelCase with use prefix (`useClipboard.ts`)
- Utils: camelCase (`clipboard.ts`, `links.ts`)
- Types: camelCase (`gameTypes.ts`)

### Code
- Components: PascalCase (`Hero`, `AppHeader`)
- Composables: camelCase (`useThreeGame`)
- Interfaces: PascalCase (`GameState`)
- Type aliases: PascalCase (`GameConfig`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (`MAX_ITEMS`)
- Functions/variables: camelCase

## ESLint Configuration
Stylistic rules:
- No trailing commas (`commaDangle: 'never'`)
- 1TBS brace style (`braceStyle: '1tbs'`)

## Performance Guidelines
- Use `defineAsyncComponent` for heavy components
- Lazy load non-critical modules
- Use `NuxtImg` for optimized images
- Use `shallowRef` for non-reactive complex objects
- Properly dispose of resources in `onUnmounted`

## Available Composables
Auto-imported from @vueuse/nuxt:
- `useClipboard`, `useDark`, `useToggle`
- `useScroll`, `useIntersectionObserver`
- `useMouse`, `useWindowSize`
- And many more from VueUse

## MCP Tools Available
When working with this project, use these MCP tools:
- **Nuxt documentation**: For Nuxt-specific questions
- **Nuxt UI**: For component documentation, props, slots, and examples
- **Figma**: For design context and screenshots

## Landing Page Components Pattern

### Section with Motion animations
```vue
<section class="py-16 sm:py-24 relative">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <Motion
      :initial="{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }"
      :while-in-view="{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }"
      :transition="{ duration: 0.5 }"
      :in-view-options="{ once: true }"
    >
      <!-- Content -->
    </Motion>
  </div>
</section>
```

### Button with Status Indicator
```vue
<UButton :color="isActive ? 'success' : 'error'" variant="ghost">
  <template #leading>
    <span class="relative flex size-2">
      <span class="absolute inline-flex size-full rounded-full opacity-75 animate-ping bg-success" />
      <span class="relative inline-flex size-2 rounded-full bg-success" />
    </span>
  </template>
  Status Label
</UButton>
```

### Gradient Text
```vue
<span class="bg-linear-to-r from-violet-500 via-fuchsia-500 to-orange-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
  Gradient Text
</span>
```
